First you need tcl tk  (tix optional)
(if you do not have it, it is probably not the software for you)

and Xotcl (see. http://www.xotcl.org)

Than adapt the file
XotclIDE

first line 

#!/usr/local/bin/xowish


 
You can also start the application by

>$ xowish XotclIDE

if you are tcl programer you know what to do
see the short docu in docs directory
